---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for FlowHat Blog">
	<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog is a content publication about LLMs, AI agents, coding tools, and practical workflows.
		This page explains what information may be collected when you visit the site and how third-party
		services may process that information.
	</p>

	<h2>Information we collect</h2>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog does not currently offer user accounts, comments, paid memberships, or on-site forms.
		That means the site does not directly ask visitors to create an account or submit personal profile
		information.
	</p>
	<p>
		Like most websites, the site may still process basic technical information through hosting,
		analytics, advertising, and security services. This can include information such as page views,
		referring pages, browser type, device type, approximate location, IP address, and interaction data.
	</p>

	<h2>Analytics and measurement</h2>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog uses analytics tools to understand traffic, improve site structure, and decide which
		content is useful to readers. The site may use:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Cloudflare Web Analytics</li>
		<li>Google Analytics</li>
		<li>Microsoft Clarity</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		These services may use cookies, scripts, or similar technologies to measure visits and site usage.
		The information is used to understand aggregate behavior, troubleshoot the site, and improve the
		publication.
	</p>

	<h2>Advertising and Google AdSense</h2>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog may use Google AdSense or other advertising services to display ads. Google and its
		partners may use cookies or similar technologies to serve ads, measure ad performance, and help
		prevent fraud and abuse.
	</p>
	<p>
		Google may use information from visits to this and other sites to provide personalized or
		non-personalized advertising, depending on visitor settings, location, consent requirements, and
		Google's policies.
	</p>
	<p>
		Visitors can learn more about how Google uses information from sites or apps that use Google
		services at <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's partner sites policy page</a>.
		Visitors can also manage ad personalization through <a href="https://myadcenter.google.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google My Ad Center</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>Affiliate and outbound links</h2>
	<p>
		FlowHat Blog may link to software vendors, marketplaces, documentation pages, GitHub repositories,
		or other third-party websites. Some outbound links may be affiliate links now or in the future. If
		an affiliate relationship exists, FlowHat Blog may earn a commission from qualifying purchases at no
		extra cost to the visitor.
	</p>
	<p>
		Third-party websites have their own privacy practices. FlowHat Blog is not responsible for the
		content, policies, or data practices of external sites.
	</p>

	<h2>Cookies and browser controls</h2>
	<p>
		Visitors can control cookies through their browser settings. Blocking some cookies or scripts may
		affect analytics, advertising, embedded content, or other site features, but the main editorial
		content should remain readable.
	</p>

	<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
	<p>
		This policy may be updated as the site changes, especially if new analytics, advertising,
		affiliate, or contact features are added. Material updates will be reflected on this page.
	</p>

	<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 4, 2026</p>
</PageLayout>
